				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: aplification<a name="20270"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 10 04 1:30 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Really depends what level you are.  At 65 with IM3 and SM2, I don't use it often.  It specifically only affects singing-based songs, not those based on instruments.    Right now, if I have the Crowned Staff of Anguish equipped plus the Harmonize effect of Shadowsong cloak, my multiplier is already 3.3 with SM2 and it caps at 3.4 -- amplification would essentially be a wasted song slot.  However if I was justing epic only without AAs, then my multiplier for singing would be 1.8 and having Amp bump that up to 2.8 on Psalm of Veeshan, for instance, would be worth the trouble.  In Hard LDON missions, I also tend to use Niv's Harmonic on our main tank and that, too, is singing based.  But again, with the other multipliers in place, amp would be a waste.</span></td>
